==English==

===Pronunciation===
*wīn, /waɪn/, /waIn/
*:'''Homophones''': [[wine]]
*hwīn, /ʍaɪn/, /WaIn/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|whine|whines}}
#a [[long-drawn]], [[high-pitched]] [[complain]]ing [[cry]] or [[sound]]
====Translations====
*German: [[Jaulen]] ''n'', [[Heulen]] ''n'', [[Jammern]] ''n''

===Verb===
{{en-verb|whine|whines|whined|whining}}
#to utter a whine
#:''The jet engines '''whined''' at take off.''
#to complain or protest in a childish manner or about trivial things
#:''The dog was '''whining''' outside the door to be let in.''
====Translations====
*German: [[jaulen]] (1,2), [[heulen]] (1,2), [[jammern]] (1,2), [[quengeln]] (2)

